text: Mohamed Haji Ibrahim Egal (August 15, 1928 â€“ May 3, 2002) was a Somalia politician who served as the President of Somaliland from 1993 to his death in 2002. He previously served as the first Prime Minister of the Somali Republic for eleven days in 1960 and again from 1967 to 1969. Egal died on May 3, 2002 in Pretoria, South Africa at the age of 73. ==References== Category:1928 births Category:2002 deaths Category:Presidents of Somaliland Category:Prime ministers of Somalia
